				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$K$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M148"><mml:mi>K</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2023_5627_Article_IEq63.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>) from 2 to 10, and measured how the power of LS changes depending on <inline-formula id="IEq64"><alternatives><tex-math id="M149">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$e$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M150"><mml:mi>e</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2023_5627_Article_IEq64.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> and <inline-formula id="IEq65"><alternatives><tex-math id="M151">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$K$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M152"><mml:mi>K</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2023_5627_Article_IEq65.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>.</p>
      <p id="Par36">Figure <xref rid="Fig2" ref-type="fig">2</xref>A and <xref rid="Fig2" ref-type="fig">B</xref> show the power difference between the original LS method and the LS method with correlation errors (LSE in short). As expected, the power difference became greater as the error (<inline-formula id="IEq66"><alternatives><tex-math id="M153">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
