				\begin{document}$$K\times K$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M164"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>K</mml:mi><mml:mo>×</mml:mo><mml:mi>K</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2023_5627_Article_IEq71.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> correlation matrix.<fig id="Fig2"><label>Fig. 2</label><caption><p>Power difference between the original LS method and the LS method with correlation errors (LSE) for <bold>A</bold> risk (left) and <bold>B</bold> protective (right) alleles, respectively. The correlation errors <inline-formula id="IEq60"><alternatives><tex-math id="M165">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
